         <description>Harold Adams was born around 1946 in Golden Meadow, La., to Andrew Adams
            and Letucia Johnfroe Adams. He grew up on Bobs Lane and attended Golden Meadow School
            and Nicholls State University as a commuter student. He married his wife, Louise Adams,
            in 1969; they were both teachers. Adams taught at Golden Meadow School, returned to
            Nicholls to get a master's degree in guidance and psychology, then was asked to be
            assistant principal of Golden Meadow. A year later he was promoted to principal, a
            position in which he stayed until he became a supervisor with federal programs, and
            retired from education after 33 years. Harold and Louise Adams are practicing Catholics,
            have two children and a number of grandchildren.; Louise Adams was born in Larose, La.,
            to a family of grocers. She attended Nicholls State University and was a teacher. She
            married Harold Adams in 1969.</description>
